<h2 id="commit-messages">Commit Messages</h2>
<h3 id="skip-a-build-—-ci-skip-or-skip-ci">Skip a build — <code>[ci skip]</code> or <code>[skip ci]</code></h3>
<p>CircleCI supports the <code>[ci skip]</code> or <code>[skip ci]</code> standard for ignoring builds.</p>
<p>CircleCI won’t run the build if they find <code>[ci skip]</code> or <code>[skip ci]</code> anywhere in the commit message of the head commit.</p>
<h3 id="pivotaltracker-integration-—-seefinishesfixesdelivers-tracker_story_idh">PivotalTracker Integration — <code>[(See|Finishes|Fixes|Delivers) #TRACKER_STORY_ID]h</code></h3>
<p>PivotalTracker/Github integration allows you to update user stories automatically.</p>
<p>To update a user story, tag your commit message in following format:</p>
<p><code>[Finishes #TRACKER_STORY_ID]</code><br>
<code>[Fixes #TRACKER_STORY_ID]</code><br>
<code>[Delivers #TRACKER_STORY_ID]</code><br>
<code>[See #TRACKER_STORY_ID]</code></p>
